text = "[b]K-Means Color Quantization Explanation:[/b]

[color=blue]Row 1[/color] shows how k-means clustering reduces the color palette of the Ada Lovelace portrait from ~100+ original colors down to 2, 5, 10, and 15 colors. The algorithm groups similar colors together and replaces them with cluster centroids.

[color=green]Row 2[/color] demonstrates how pixel resolution affects quantization results. Lower resolutions (8x8) lose detail but can still capture the essence with just 5 colors, while higher resolutions (64x64) preserve more detail.

[color=purple]Row 3[/color] displays the actual color palettes extracted by k-means. These centroids represent the most significant colors in the image - notice how skin tones, hair colors, and dress colors are preserved as separate clusters.

[b]Algorithm Process:[/b]
1. Initialize k random centroids in RGB color space
2. Assign each pixel to nearest centroid
3. Update centroids to mean of assigned pixels
4. Repeat steps 2-3 until convergence
5. Replace all pixels with their centroid colors"
